But let's say you have a data set that's like a couple of terabytes or something and you've

00:49:43.139 --> 00:49:48.139
got it in memory and are when you first declare the recipe, you can just take the first

00:49:48.139 --> 00:49:53.659
hundred data points, let's say, from that that that big data set and use that to define

00:49:53.659 --> 00:50:00.459
the recipe, because the only thing that the original recipe does is is get an accounting

00:50:00.459 --> 00:50:03.500
